This paper deals with optimizing packet scheduling in wireless relay networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves stochastic modeling and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the use of stochastic dominance and coupling arguments indicates a connection to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
